// Datasheet for the `cache` device: it also requires the `key`/`val` components and storage for a
// `Node` shape, minimum 16 rows. This is the SAME shared shape the `store` device uses — devices share
// shapes by structure. A datasheet defines no shape; the driver defines `Node` and must provide ONE
// pool that meets the max of the two minimums. Support file.
// RUN: true
key :: float;
val :: float;
[16]Node;
